Hey Everyone,
Just thought id demo something that i have set up in my app

With the custom code area in the climbo brand page you can input some code that can add elements to your app. We know that, for live chat, widget etc

However you can also use it to place html in which can inherit the styling and css of your app by default. This allows us to acheive things like custom nav menu items that look fully native! in this case the help center!

Let me know your thoughts i hope it helps some people!

The code it below:
<script>
\(function\(\) {
// === SIDEBAR MENU FUNCTION ===
function addSidebarHelpCenter\(\) {
if \(document.querySelector\('.custom-help-center-link'\)\) {
return true;
}

const settingsLink = document.querySelector\('a\[href="#/settings"\]'\);

if \(settingsLink\) {
const helpCenterHTML = `
<a class="w-full custom-help-center-link" href="[https://knowledge-base.help/](https://knowledge-base.help/)" target="_blank">
<div class="rounded-ds-corners transition-all inline-flex items-center justify-center min-w-5 h-10 active:scale-95 bg-ds-menu-btn-inactive hover:bg-ds-hover-menu-btn-inactive text-ds-menu-btn-inactive hover:text-ds-hover-menu-btn-inactive font-normal BaseMenuButton w-full">
<div class="inline-flex items-center justify-start flex-nowrap relative h-10 gap-4 px-4 w-full">
<svg width="1em" height="1em" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" xmlns="[http://www.w3.org/2000/svg](http://www.w3.org/2000/svg)" class="BaseMenuButtonIcon text-\[1rem\]">
<path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M12 2C6.477 2 2 6.477 2 12s4.477 10 10 10 10-4.477 10-10S17.523 2 12 2zM0 12C0 5.373 5.373 0 12 0s12 5.373 12 12-5.373 12-12 12S0 18.627 0 12zm13 7a1 1 0 11-2 0 1 1 0 012 0zm-1-3a1 1 0 01-1-1v-1.5a1 1 0 011-1 2 2 0 10-2-2 1 1 0 01-2 0 4 4 0 114 4 1 1 0 01-1 1v1.5a1 1 0 01-1 1z" fill="currentColor"/>
</svg>
<div class="text-\[1rem\] leading-\[1.25rem\] Typography BaseMenuButtonLabel relative font-normal text-\[inherit\]">Help Center</div>
</div>
</div>
</a>
`;

settingsLink.insertAdjacentHTML\('beforebegin', helpCenterHTML\);

I'm using the client version with the left column, and I found my logo was too small and not centered!

So, I tried modifying the style with a little CSS code, and here's the result on the GIF 😉

For those interested, here's my code to add in "custom code" in "brand" agency menu:

<style>
/* Image */
.sidebar .justify-start img{
transform:scale\(1.7\) translatex\(20px\);
}
@media \(min-width:1024px\) and \(max-width:1279px\){
.sidebar .justify-start img{
transform:scale\(2\) translatex\(1px\);
}
}
</style>

Tips :
You might need to modify it if your logo is a different size than this example 600x171px
You can adjust the logo size with the "scale" value
You can adjust the horizontal position with the "translatex" value
